# Interpreter for 'vpn-switch wireguard info' command
# Terminal function that outputs category information directly to user
#
# Default value: "cat"
#   Outputs category details directly to stdout (no execution needed)
#   Shows category metadata, path, and contents
#
# This is a terminal/display function - it should NOT execute commands.
# Use 'cat' to send output directly to the user without interpretation.
#
# Example output:
#   # Category: privacy
#   # Path: /path/to/database/wireguard/privacy
#   # Contents:
#   #   ch1 -> ../wg-CH-1.conf
#   #   rs1 -> ../wg-RS-1.conf
